'''男性避孕'''是指由男性進行的[[生育控制|生育控制]]方式。主要的男性避孕方式有[[避孕套|避孕套]]、[[体外排精|性交中斷法]]、[[非插入式性行為|非插入式性行為]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.plannedparenthood.org/health-topics/mens-sexual-health/birth-control-men-22600.htm |title=Birth Control for Men | How Can Men Prevent Pregnancy? |publisher=Plannedparenthood.org |date=2015-12-28 |accessdate=2017-03-17 |archive-date=2014-04-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140409050214/http://www.plannedparenthood.org/health-topics/mens-sexual-health/birth-control-men-22600.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>及[[输精管切除术|输精管切除术]]<ref name=methods>{{cite journal | pmid = 20933119 | doi=10.1016/j.contraception.2010.03.016 | volume=82 | issue=5 | title=Acceptability of contraception for men: a review |date=2010-11 | author=Glasier A | journal=Contraception | pages=453–6}}</ref>。還有其他男性避孕方式，不過尚在[[研究開發|研究開發]]階段，暫未商品化<ref>{{cite web |last=Schieszer |first=John |url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/3543478/ |title=Male birth control pill soon a reality - Health - Sexual health - Men's Sexual Health Guide | NBC News |publisher=MSNBC |date=2003-10-01 |accessdate=2017-03-17 |archive-date=2012-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121114165255/http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/3543478/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。其中像是{{le|RISUG|Reversible inhibition of sperm under guidance|RISUG/VasalGel}}（已在印度完成第二階段的人類臨床實驗，正在進行第三階段）<ref>{{cite journal|last=Guha|first=Sujoy|author2=Singh G |author3=Ansari S |author4=Kumar S |author5=Srivastava A |author6=Koul V |author7=Das HC |author8=Malhotra RL |author9=Das SK.  |title=Phase II clinical trial of a vas deferens injectable contraceptive for the male|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_contraception_1997-10_56_4/page/245|journal=Contraception|date=1997-10|pages=245–50|pmid=9408706|volume=56|issue=4|doi=10.1016/s0010-7824(97)00142-x}}</ref>及[[超聲波|超聲波]]（目前只進行到動物實驗<ref name="bare_url"/><ref name="Tsuruta">{{cite journal|last=Tsuruta|first=James K.|author2=Dayton PA, Gallippi CM, O'Rand MG, Streicker MA, Gessner RC, Gregory TS, Silva EJ, Hamil KG, Moser GJ, Sokal DC.|title=Therapeutic ultrasound as a potential male contraceptive: power, frequency and temperature required to deplete rat testes of meiotic cells and epididymides of sperm determined using a commercially available system|journal=Reprod. Biol. Endocrinol.|date=2012-01-30|volume=10|issue=7|doi=10.1186/1477-7827-10-7|pmid=22289508|url=http://www.rbej.com/content/10/1/7|pmc=3340307|pages=7|access-date=2017-03-02|archive-date=2015-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151029214034/http://www.rbej.com/content/10/1/7|dead-url=no}}</ref>）。

